-- Kirayaka Bank, Sendai Bank May Merge Under Holding Company, NHK Reports
-- B y   T a k   K u m a k u r a
-- 2010-10-24T21:27:30Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-24/kirayaka-bank-sendai-bank-may-merge-under-holding-company-nhk-reports.html
Kirayaka Bank Ltd., a Japanese
regional bank based in Yamagata City, is in merger talks with
closely held Sendai Bank, public broadcaster NHK said, citing an
unidentified person familiar with the situation.   The banks will merge under a holding company during the
next fiscal year, the report said.    To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Takehiko Kumakura at 
 tkumakura@bloomberg.net  